The defendant Blair L. Thompson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Manuf/Deliver Schedule I, II Narcotics, a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(a).
  • Manuf/Deliver Schedule I, II Narcotics, a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.
No DNA sample is ordered as Defendant previously provided the same through another felony conviction.
Defendant to undergo an alcohol and other drug assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.

supervisions.notes: Concurrent with: Waushara Co Case No. 2018CF000032 - Count No. 1.

superMiscConds.notes: The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.
Defendant to undergo an alcohol and other drug assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.

Costs reimposed as to Count Nos. 1 and 2 to the extent not previously paid in the amount of $746.00.  The defendant is ordered to authorize the Department of Corrections to collect from the defendant's wages and from other moneys held in the defendant's prisoner's account, an amount or percentage the department determines is reasonable for payment to victims.  If any fines, costs, and/or restitution remain outstanding at the end of the initial confinement portion of this sentence, then the remaining shall be paid as a condition of extended supervision.

miscConds.notes: Same repayment provisions apply as noted above for Count No. 1.

16CF-33 and 18CF-32 - Both Cases Called @ 1:40 PM: Defendant Blair L. Thompson in court with attorney Katena Roberts-Turner.  Defendant Blair L. Thompson in custody.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Counsel prepared to move toward resolution today as to both matters.  Recommendation recited by DA.  Def and counsel concur matters both resolved today.   Defendant advised of potential punishment.  Defendant confirms he is able to hear properly and no device needed.  Terms of bifurcated SEH explained.   Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant - no impairment on proceeding today.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Based upon Defendant's statements the State is unsure if Def wishes to proceed to resolution on 18CF32.  Def confers w/Counsel.  Clarification by SPD as to Def's position.  Def also confirms he agrees with clarification.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  18CF-32 Plea Ct 1 w/o 961 Enh:  NC  Plea Ct 2 w/o 961 Enh:  NC  Court accepts pleas and enters JOC.  Ct 3 DRI and 961 Enh dismissed - modifier attached to Ct Nos 1 and 2.  16CF-33 SEHR:  Counsel admit receipt of Rev Order and Warrant.  No factual corrections or clarifications offered.  Chapter 950 in compliance.  Argument by DA.  Argument by SPD.  Statement by Def prior to SEH:  None offered by Def.  The Court:  16CF-33:  6 yrs bifurcated SEH - 3 yrs IC/3 yrs ES - Concurrent to one another with 166 days TS credit. 18CF-32: Ct 1 only 6  yrs bifurcated SEH  - 3 yrs IC/3 yrs ES  - concurrent with 16CF-33 - net effect is a 6 yr period of imprisonment.  3 days TS as to 18CF-32.  Eligible for SAP statutorily.  Ct 2 18CF-32 - S/W - 2 yrs probation consecutive to 16CF-33 and 18CF-32 (Ct 1).  Add'l period of oversight in the aftermath of prison SEH completion.  Conditions of ES:  Complete an AODA and any follow thru as recommended; the defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician; Court Costs to include any unfulfilled obligations as to 16CF-33 and as to Ct 1 18CF 32 an add'l cost $95 purchase money added; same conditions to apply to the period of probation ordered consecutive to period of incarceration.  DOC authorized to collect from any wages held in trust account for payment.  DNA Sample on file, Surcharge ordered by the Court.   Appeal Rights Given.
